They all looked identical, and I pondered how sad it was that though they may modify their look with a simple haircut or some other affectation, they still will don identical uniforms dedicated to destroying any semblance of identity they had created. But one had struck my eye. I watched him as he put on his helmet, and realized he had decorated it. The deep green and silver was like nothing I had seen, and I smiled to myself.
